quran[246]{c,v,t}:
  41,47,"To Him is referred the knowledge of the Hour: and no fruits come forth from their husks, and no female conceives, or is delivered, save with His knowledge. And the day when He shall call to them, 'Where are the partners ye did join with me"
  41,48,"they shall say, 'We do own to thee there is no witness amongst us!' and that on which they used to call before shall stray away from them, and they shall think there is no escape for them"
  41,49,"Man is never tired of praying for good, but if evil touch him, then he is despairing and hopeless"
  41,50,"But if we make him taste mercy from us after distress has touched him he will surely say, 'This is for me, and I do not think the Hour is imminent; and if I be brought back to my Lord, verily, I shall surely have good with Him;' but we will inform those who misbelieve of what they have done, and we will surely make them taste wretched torment"
  41,51,"And when we have been gracious to man, he turns away and goes aside; but when evil touches him he is one of copious prayer"
  41,52,"Say, 'Let us see now! if it be from God and ye disbelieve in it, who is more in error than he who is in a remote schism"
  41,53,"We will show them our signs in the regions and in themselves, until it is plain to them that it is the truth. Is it not enough for thy Lord that He is witness over all"
  41,54,"Ay, verily, they are in doubt about the meeting of their Lord! Ay, verily, He encompasses all"
  42,1,M
  42,2,Q
  42,3,"Thus does God, the mighty, the wise, inspire thee and those before thee"
  42,4,"His is what is in the heavens and what is in the earth, and He is the high, the mighty"
  42,5,"The heavens well-nigh cleave asunder from above them; and the angels celebrate the praises of their Lord, and ask forgiveness for those who are on the earth. Ay, verily, God, He is the forgiving and merciful"
  42,6,"but those who take beside Him patrons, God watches over them, and thou hast not charge over them"
  42,7,"Thus have we revealed an Arabic Qur'an, that thou mayest warn the Mother of cities and all around it; and warn them of a day of gathering, there is no doubt therein;- a part in Paradise and a part in the blaze"
  42,8,But had God pleased He would have made them one nation; but He makes whom He will enter into His mercy; and the unjust have neither patron nor help
  42,9,"Do they take other patrons besides Him, when God He is the patron, and He quickens the dead and He is mighty over all"
  42,10,"But whatsoever ye dispute about, the judgment of it is God's. There is God for you!- my Lord! upon Him do I rely, and unto Him I turn repentant"
  42,11,"The originator of the heavens and the earth, He has made for you from yourselves wives; and of the cattle mates; producing you thereby. There is naught like Him, for He both hears and sees"
  42,12,"His are the keys of the heavens and the earth, He extends provision to whom He will, or doles it out; verily, He knows everything"
  42,13,"He has enjoined upon you for religion what He prescribed to Noah and what we inspired thee with, and what we inspired Abraham and Moses and Jesus,- to be steadfast in religion, and not to part into sects therein - a great thing to the idolaters is that which ye call them to! God elects for Himself whom He pleases and guides unto Himself him who turns repentant"
  42,14,"But they did not part into sects until after the knowledge had come to them, through mutual envy; and had it not been for thy Lord's word already passed for an appointed time, it would surely have been decided between them; but, verily, those who have been given the Book as an inheritance after them, are in hesitating doubt concerning it"
  42,15,"Wherefore call thou, and go straight on as thou art bidden, and follow not their lusts; and say, 'I believe in the Book which God has sent down; and I am bidden to judge justly between you. God is our Lord and your Lord; we have our works and ye have your works; there is no argument between us and you. God will assemble us together and unto Him the journey is"
  42,16,"But those who argue about God after it has been assented to, their arguments shall be rebutted before their Lord; and upon them shall be wrath, and for them shall be keen torment"
  42,17,"God it is who has sent down the Book with truth, and the balance; and what shall make thee know whether haply the Hour be nigh"
  42,18,"Those who believe not would hurry it on; and those who believe shrink with terror at it and know that it is true. Ay, verily, those who dispute concerning the Hour are in remote error"
  42,19,"God is kind to His servants; He Provides whom He will, and He is the mighty, the glorious"
  42,20,"He who wishes for the tilth of the next world, we will increase for him the tilth; and he who desires the tilth of this world, we will give him thereof: but in the next he shall have no portion"
  42,21,"Have they associates who have enjoined any religion on them which God permits not?- but were it not for the word of decision it would have been decreed to them. Verily, the unjust,- for them is grievous woe"
  42,22,"Thou shalt see the unjust shrink with terror from what they have gained as it falls upon them; and those who believe and do right, in meads of Paradise, they shall have what they please with their Lord;- that is great grace"
  42,23,"That is what God gives glad tidings of to His servants who believe and do righteous acts. Say, 'I do not ask for it a hire - only the love of my kinsfolk.' And he who gains a good action we will increase good for him thereby; verily, God is forgiving and grateful"
  42,24,"Or will they say he has forged against God a lie? But if God pleased He could set a seal upon thy heart; but God will blot out falsehood and verify truth by His word; verily, He knows the nature of men's breasts"
  42,25,He it is who accepts repentance from His servants and pardons their offences and knows that which ye do
  42,26,"And He answers the prayer of those who believe and do right, and gives them increase of His grace; but the misbelievers,- for them is keen torment"
  42,27,"And if God were to extend provision to His servants they would be wanton in the earth. But He sends down by measure what He pleases; verily, of His servants He is well aware and sees"
  42,28,"He it is who sends down the rain after they have despaired; and disperses His mercy, for He is the praiseworthy patron"
  42,29,"And of His signs is the creation of the heavens and the earth, and what He hath spread abroad therein of beasts; and He is able to collect them when He will"
  42,30,And what misfortunes befall you it is for what your hands have earned; but He pardons much
  42,31,"yet ye cannot make Him helpless in the earth, nor have ye, besides God, either a patron or a helper"
  42,32,And of His signs are the ships that sail like mountains in the sea
  42,33,"If He will, He calms the wind, and they become motionless on the back thereof: verily, in that are signs to every patient, grateful person"
  42,34,or He makes them founder for what they have earned; but He pardons much
  42,35,But let those who wrangle about our signs know that they shall have no escape
  42,36,And whatever ye are given it is but a provision of the life of this world; but what is with God is better and more lasting for those who believe and who upon their Lord rely
  42,37,"and those who avoid great sins and abominations, and who when they are wroth forgive"
  42,38,"and who assent to their Lord, and are steadfast in prayer, and whose affairs go by counsel amongst themselves, and who of what we have bestowed on them give alms"
  42,39,"and who, when wrong befalls them, help themselves"
  42,40,"For the recompence of evil is evil like unto it; but he who pardons and does well, then his reward is with God; verily, He loves not the unjust"
  42,41,"And he who helps himself after he has been wronged, for these - there is no way against them"
  42,42,The way is only against those who wrong men and are wanton in the earth without right; these - for them is grievous woe
  42,43,"But surely he who is patient and forgives,- verily, that is a determined affair"
  42,44,"But whomsoever God leads astray he has no patron after Him; and thou mayest see the unjust when they see the torment say, 'Is there no way to avert this"
  42,45,"and thou mayest see them exposed to it, humbled with abasement, looking with a stealthy glance. And those who believe shall say, 'Verily the losers are they who have lost themselves and their family's too upon the resurrection day!' Ay, verily, the unjust are in lasting torment"
  42,46,"And they shall have no patrons to help them beside God, and whomsoever God leads astray, there is no way for him"
  42,47,Assent to your Lord before the day comes of which there is no averting from God; there is no refuge for you on that day; and for you there is no denial
  42,48,"But if they turn aside, we have not sent thee to them as a guardian, thou hast only thy message to preach. And, verily, when we have made man taste of mercy from us he rejoices therein; but if there befall them an evil for what their hands have done before - then, verily, man is ungrateful"
  42,49,"God's is the kingdom of the heavens and the earth, He creates what He pleases, He grants to whom He pleases females, and He grants to whom He pleases males, or He gives them in pairs, males and females"
  42,50,"and He makes whom He pleases barren; verily, He is knowing, powerful"
  42,51,"It is not for any mortal that God should speak to him, except by inspiration, or from behind a veil, or by sending an apostle and inspiring, by His permission, what He pleases; verily, He is high and wise"
  42,52,"And thus have we inspired thee by a spirit at our bidding; thou didst not know what the Book was, nor the faith: but we made it a light whereby we guide whom we will of our servants. And, verily, thou shalt surely be guided into the right way"
  42,53,"the way of God, whose is what is in the heavens and what is in the earth. Ay, to God affairs do tend"
  43,1,M
  43,2,By the perspicuous Book
  43,3,"verily, we have made it an Arabic Qur'an; haply ye will have some sense"
  43,4,"And it is in the Mother of the Book with us,- high and wise"
  43,5,"Shall we then push aside from you the Reminder, because ye are a people who are extravagant"
  43,6,How many prophets have we sent amongst those of yore
  43,7,and there never came to them a prophet but they did mock at him
  43,8,then we destroyed them - more valiant than these; and the example of those of yore passed away
  43,9,"And if thou shouldst ask them who created the heavens and the earth, they will surely say, 'The mighty, the knowing One created them"
  43,10,"who made for you the earth a couch and placed for you therein roads, haply ye may be guided"
  43,11,and who sent down from the heaven water in due measure; and we raised up thereby a dead country; thus shall ye too be brought forth
  43,12,and who has created all species; and has made for you the ships and the cattle whereon to ride
  43,13,"that ye may settle yourselves on their backs; then remember the favour of your Lord when ye settled thereon, and say, 'Celebrated be the praises of Him who hath subjected this to us! We could not have got this ourselves"
  43,14,"and, verily, unto our Lord shall we return"
  43,15,"Yet they make for Him of His servants offspring; verily, man is surely obviously ungrateful"
  43,16,"Has He taken of what He creates daughters, and chosen sons for you"
  43,17,"Yet when the tidings are given any one of that which he strikes out as a similitude for the Merciful One, his face grows black and he is choked"
  43,18,"What! one brought up amongst ornaments, and who is always in contention without obvious cause"
  43,19,"And have they made the angels, who are the servants of the Merciful One, females? Were they witnesses of their creation? their witness shall be written down, and they shall be questioned"
  43,20,"and they say, 'Had the Merciful pleased we should never have worshipped them.' They have no knowledge of that, they only conjecture"
  43,21,Have we given them a book before it to which they might hold
  43,22,"Nay; they say, 'We found our fathers (agreed) upon a religion, and, verily, we are guided by their traces"
  43,23,"Thus, too, did we never send before thee to a city any warner, but the affluent ones thereof said, 'Verily, we found our fathers (agreed) upon a religion, and, verily, we are led by their traces"
  43,24,"Say, 'What! if I come to you with what is a better guide than what ye found your fathers agreed upon?' and they will say, 'Verily, we, in what ye are sent with disbelieve"
  43,25,"Then we took vengeance on them, and see how was the end of those who called the (apostles) liars"
  43,26,"When Abraham said to his father and his people, 'Verily, I am clear of all that ye serve"
  43,27,"except Him who created me; for, verily, He will guide me"
  43,28,"and he made it a word remaining among his posterity, that haply they might return"
  43,29,"Nay; but I let these (Meccans) and their fathers have enjoyment until the truth came to them, and an apostle"
  43,30,"And when the truth came to them they said, 'This is magic, and we therein do disbelieve"
  43,31,"And they say, 'Unless this Qur'an were sent down to a man great in the two cities"
  43,32,"Is it they who distribute the mercy of thy Lord? We distribute amongst them their livelihood in the life of this world, and we exalt some of them above others in degrees, that some may take others into subjection; but the mercy of thy Lord is better than that which they amass"
  43,33,"And but that men would then have been one nation, we would have made for those who misbelieve in the Merciful One roofs of silver for their houses, and steps up thereto which they might mount"
  43,34,"and to their houses doors, and bedsteads on which they might recline"
  43,35,"and gilding,- for, verily, all that is a provision of the life of this world, but the hereafter is better with thy Lord for those who fear"
  43,36,"And whosoever turns from the reminder of the Merciful One, we will chain to him a devil, who shall be his mate"
  43,37,"and, verily these shall turn them from the path while they reckon that they are guided"
  43,38,"until when he comes to us he shall say, 'O, would that between me and thee there were the distance of the two orients, for an evil mate (art thou)"
  43,39,"But it shall not avail you on that day, since ye were unjust; verily, in the torment shall ye share"
  43,40,"What! canst thou make the deaf to hear, or guide the blind, or him who is in obvious error"
  43,41,Whether then we take thee off we will surely take vengeance on them
  43,42,"or whether we show thee that which we have promised them; for, verily, we have power over them"
  43,43,"Say, 'Dost thou hold to what is inspired thee?' verily, thou art in the right way"
  43,44,"and, verily, it is a reminder to thee and to thy people, but in the end they shall be asked"
  43,45,"And ask those whom we have sent before thee amongst the prophets, 'Did we make gods beside the Merciful One for them to serve"
  43,46,"We did send Moses with our signs to Pharaoh and his chiefs, and he said, 'Verily, I am the apostle of the Lord of the worlds"
  43,47,"but when he came to them with our signs, lo, they laughed at them"
  43,48,"And we did not show them a sign, but it was greater than its fellow; and we seized them with the torment, haply they might turn"
  43,49,"And they said, 'O thou magician! pray for us to thy Lord, as He has engaged with thee: verily, we are guided"
  43,50,"And when we removed from them the torment, behold they broke their word"
  43,51,"And Pharaoh proclaimed amongst his people; said he, 'O my people! is not the kingdom of Egypt mine? and these rivers that flow beneath me? What! can ye then not see"
  43,52,"Am I better than this fellow, who is contemptible, who can hardly explain himself"
  43,53,"Unless then bracelets of gold be cast upon him, or there come with him angels as his mates"
  43,54,"And he taught his people levity; and they obeyed him: verily, they were an abominable people"
  43,55,"And when they had annoyed us we took vengeance on them, and we drowned them all together"
  43,56,and we made them a precedent and an example to those after them
  43,57,"And when the son of Mary was set forth as a parable, behold thy people turned away from him"
  43,58,"and said, 'Are our gods better, or is he?' They did not set it forth to thee save for wrangling. Nay, but they are a contentious people"
  43,59,"He is but a servant whom we have been gracious to, and we have made him an example for the children of Israel"
  43,60,And if we please we can make of you angels in the earth to succeed you
  43,61,"And, verily, he is a sign of the Hour. Doubt not then concerning it, but follow this right way"
  43,62,"and let not the devil turn you away; verily, he is to you an open foe"
  43,63,"And when Jesus came with manifest signs he said, 'I am come to you with wisdom, and I will explain to you something of that whereon ye did dispute, then fear God, obey me"
  43,64,"verily, God, He is my Lord and your Lord, serve Him then, this is the right way"
  43,65,But the confederates disputed amongst themselves; and woe to those who are unjust from the torment of a grievous day
  43,66,Do they expect aught but that the Hour will come upon them suddenly while they do not perceive
  43,67,"Friends on that day shall be foes to each other, save those who fear"
  43,68,O my servants! there is no fear for you on that day; nor shall ye be grieved
  43,69,who believe in our signs and who are resigned
  43,70,"Enter ye into Paradise, ye and your wives, happy"
  43,71,"Dishes of gold and pitchers shall be sent round to them; therein is what souls desire, and eyes shall be delighted, and ye therein shall dwell for aye"
  43,72,for that is Paradise which ye are given as an inheritance for that which ye have done
  43,73,Therein shall ye have much fruit whereof to eat
  43,74,"Verily, the sinners are in the torment of hell to dwell for aye"
  43,75,"It shall not be intermitted for them, and they therein shall be confused"
  43,76,"We have not wronged them, but it was themselves they wronged"
  43,77,"And they shall cry out, 'O Malik! let thy lord make an end of us;' he shall say, 'Verily, ye are to tarry here"
  43,78,"We have brought you the truth, but most of you are averse from the truth"
  43,79,Have they arranged the affair? then will we arrange it too
  43,80,"Or do they reckon that we did not hear their secrets and their whispering? Nay, but our messengers are with them writing down"
  43,81,"Say, 'If the Merciful One has a son then am I the first to worship him"
  43,82,"Celebrated be the praise of the Lord of the heavens and the earth! the Lord of the throne, above all they attribute to Him"
  43,83,But leave them to ponder and to play until they meet that day of theirs which they are promised
  43,84,"He it is who is in the heaven a God and in the earth a God! and He is the wise, the knowing"
  43,85,"And blessed be he whose is the kingdom of the heavens and the earth, and what is between both, and His is the knowledge of the Hour, and unto Him shall ye be brought back"
  43,86,And those they call on beside Him shall not possess intercession except those only who bear witness for the truth and who do know
  43,87,"And if thou shouldst ask them who created them they shall surely say, 'God!' How then can they lie"
  43,88,"And what he says, 'O Lord, verily, these are a people who do not believe"
  43,89,"shun them then and say, \"Peace!\" for they at length shall know"
  44,1,M
  44,2,By the perspicuous Book
  44,3,"verily, we have sent it down on a blessed night;- verily, we had given warning"
  44,4,wherein is decided every wise affair
  44,5,"as an order from us. Verily, we were sending (apostles)"
  44,6,"a mercy from thy Lord; verily, He both hears and knows"
  44,7,"from the Lord of the heavens and the earth and what is between the two, if ye were but sure"
  44,8,"There is no god but He, He quickens and He kills - your Lord and the Lord of your fathers of yore"
  44,9,"Nay, they in doubt do play"
  44,10,But expect thou the day when the heaven shall bring obvious smoke
  44,11,to cover men - this is grievous torment
  44,12,"Our Lord! remove from us the torment; verily, we are believers"
  44,13,"How can they have the reminder (now), when they have had a plain apostle"
  44,14,"and when they turned their backs away from him and said, 'Taught! mad"
  44,15,"Verily, we will remove the torment a little, (but) ye will surely return"
  44,16,"On the day when we will assault with the great assault, verily, we will take vengeance"
  44,17,And we already tried the people of Pharaoh when there came to them a noble apostle
  44,18,"Send back to me God's servants; verily, I am to you a faithful apostle"
  44,19,"and, 'Exalt not yourselves above God; verily, I come to you with obvious authority"
  44,20,"And, verily, I seek refuge in my Lord and your Lord, that ye stone me not"
  44,21,And if ye believe not in me then let me alone
  44,22,"Then he called upon his Lord, 'Verily, these are a sinful people"
  44,23,"So journey with my servants by night - verily, ye will be pursued"
  44,24,"But leave the sea in quiet - verily, they are a host to be drowned"
  44,25,How many gardens and springs have they left
  44,26,and corn lands and a noble place
  44,27,and comfort wherein they did enjoy themselves
  44,28,Thus - and we gave them for an inheritance to another people
  44,29,"And the heaven wept not for them, nor the earth, nor were they respited"
  44,30,But we saved the children of Israel from shameful woe
  44,31,"from Pharaoh; verily, he was haughty, one of the extravagant"
  44,32,"And we did choose them, wittingly, above the worlds"
  44,33,and we gave them signs wherein was an obvious trial
  44,34,"Verily, these say"
  44,35,It is but our first death
  44,36,"so bring our fathers, if ye do speak the truth"
  44,37,"Are they better than the people of Tubbah, and those before them? We destroyed them - verily, they were sinners"
  44,38,"Nor did we create the heavens and the earth, and what is between the two in sport"
  44,39,"we did but create them in truth, though most of them know it not"
  44,40,"Verily, the day of separation is their appointed term"
  44,41,"the day when master shall not avail client at all, nor shall they be helped"
  44,42,"save whomsoever God shall have mercy on; verily, He is the mighty, the merciful"
  44,43,"Verily, the Zaqqum tree"
  44,44,(shall be) the food of the sinful
  44,45,"as it were melting, shall it boil in their bellies"
  44,46,like the boiling of hot water
  44,47,Take him and hale him into the midst of hell
  44,48,then pour over his head the torment of hot water
  44,49,"Taste! verily, thou art the mighty, the honourable"
  44,50,"Verily, this is that whereon ye did dispute"
  44,51,"Verily, the pious shall be in a safe place"
  44,52,in gardens and springs
  44,53,they shall be clad in satin and stout silk face to face
  44,54,Thus!- and we will wed them to bright and large-eyed maids
  44,55,They shall call therein for every fruit in safety
  44,56,"They shall not taste therein of death save their first death, and we will keep them from the torment of hell"
  44,57,"Grace from thy Lord, that is the grand bliss"
  44,58,"And we have only made it easy for thy tongue, that haply they may be mindful"
  44,59,"Then watch thou; verily, they are watching too"
  45,1,M
  45,2,"A revelation of the Book from God, the mighty, the wise"
  45,3,"Verily, in the heavens and the earth are signs to those who believe"
  45,4,and in your creation and the beasts that are spread abroad are signs to a people who are sure
  45,5,"and in the alternation of night and day, and the provision that God has sent down from heaven and quickened thereby the earth after its death, and in the veering of the winds are signs unto a people who have sense"
  45,6,These are the signs of God which we recite to thee in truth; and in what new story after God and His signs will they believe
  45,7,Woe to every sinful liar
  45,8,"who hears God's signs sent to him, then persists in being big with pride as though he heard them not - so give him the glad-tidings of grievous woe"
  45,9,"and when he knows something of our signs takes them for a jest! These,- for them is shameful woe"
  45,10,"behind them is hell, and what they have earned shall not avail them aught, nor what they have taken besides God for patrons; and for them is mighty woe"
  45,11,"This is a guidance, and those who misbelieve in the signs of their Lord, for them is torment of a grievous plague"
  45,12,"God it is who subjects to you the sea that the ships may sail thereon at his bidding, and that ye may crave of His grace, and that haply ye may give thanks"
  45,13,"and He has subjected to you what is in the heavens and what is in the earth,- all from Him; verily, in that are signs unto a people who reflect"
  45,14,"Say to those who believe that they pardon those who hope not for God's days, that He may reward a people for that which they have earned"
  45,15,"Whosoever acts aright it is for his own soul, and whosoever does evil it is against it; then unto your Lord shall ye be returned"
  45,16,"And we did bring the children of Israel the Book and judgment and prophecy, and we provided them with good things, and preferred them above the worlds"
  45,17,"And we brought them manifest proofs of the affair, and they disputed not until after knowledge had come to them, through mutual envy. Verily, thy Lord will decide between them on the resurrection day concerning that whereon they did dispute"
  45,18,"Then we did set thee over a law concerning the affair: follow it then, and follow not the lusts of those who do not know"
  45,19,"Verily, they shall not avail thee against God at all; and, verily, the wrong-doers are patrons of each other, but God is the patron of those who fear"
  45,20,This is an insight for men and a guidance and a mercy to a people who are sure
  45,21,"Do those who commit evil deeds count that we will make them like those who, believe and work righteous deeds, equal in their life and their death?- ill it is they judge"
  45,22,"And God created the heavens and the earth in truth; and every soul shall be recompensed for that which it has earned, and they shall not be wronged"
  45,23,"Hast thou considered him who takes his lusts for his god, and God leads him astray wittingly, and has set a seal upon his hearing and his heart, and has placed upon his eyesight dimness? who then shall guide him after God? Will they not then mind"
  45,24,"They say, 'It is only our life in this world, we die and we live, and naught destroys us but time!' But they have no knowledge of this; they do but suspect"
  45,25,"And when our signs are rehearsed to them with evidences their only argument is to say, 'Bring our fathers, if ye speak the truth"
  45,26,"Say, 'God quickens you, then He kills you, then He will gather you unto the resurrection day, there is no doubt therein; but most men do not know"
  45,27,"God's is the kingdom of the heavens and the earth, and on the day when the Hour shall arise on that day shall those who call it vain be losers"
  45,28,"And thou shalt see each nation kneeling, each nation summoned to its book, 'Today are ye rewarded for that which ye have done"
  45,29,"This is our Book that speaketh to you with truth; verily, we have written down what ye have done"
  45,30,"But as to those who believe and do righteous deeds their Lord will make them enter into His mercy, that is the obvious bliss"
  45,31,"And as for those who misbelieve,- were not my signs recited to you and ye were too big with pride and ye were a sinful people"
  45,32,"And when it was said, 'Verily, the promise of God is true, and the Hour there is no doubt therein;' ye said, 'We know not what the Hour is, we only suspect, and we are not sure"
  45,33,"But there shall appear to them the evils of what they have done, and that shall encompass them at which they have been mocking"
  45,34,"And it shall be said, 'Today will we forget you as ye forgat the meeting of this day of yours, and your resort shall be the fire, and ye shall have no helpers"
  45,35,"That is because ye took the signs of God for a jest and the life of this world deceived you; wherefore today ye shall not be brought forth therefrom, neither shall ye be taken back into favour"
  45,36,"God's then is the praise, the Lord of the heavens and the Lord of the earth, the Lord of the worlds"
  45,37,"His is the grandeur in the heavens and the earth, and He is the mighty and the wise"